<!--
pr-body.md.template
Purpose: Generates structured pull request descriptions for GitHub PRs
Scope: All pull requests in the homelab-cluster repository
Overview: Provides a four-section PR body format that gives reviewers sufficient context
    to understand, evaluate, and approve changes. Sections cover what changed and why,
    a detailed change list, risk assessment, and observable behavioral impact. HTML
    comments within each section provide fill-in guidance and are invisible when rendered
    on GitHub.

Placeholders:
  {{EXECUTIVE_SUMMARY}}: High-level description of the change and its motivation
    - Type: string
    - Example: "Adds a new app deployment for seminary-feedback behind Cloudflare Tunnel"
    - Required: yes

  {{LIST_OF_CHANGES}}: Bulleted list of logical changes grouped by file/module/concern
    - Type: string (markdown bullet list)
    - Example: "- Add `apps/seminary-feedback/manifest.yaml` — namespace, deployment, service, ingress"
    - Required: yes

  {{RISK_LEVEL}}: One of the predefined risk levels with brief explanation
    - Type: string
    - Example: "Feature addition — adds new files; no existing behavior modified"
    - Required: yes

  {{NEW_BEHAVIOR}}: Observable effect after merging
    - Type: string
    - Example: "Seminary feedback app accessible at seminary.mlops-club.org"
    - Required: yes

Usage:
  1. Read this template when creating a PR
  2. Fill in all four sections based on the diff and commit history
  3. Pass the filled content as the --body argument to gh pr create
  4. Do not include this header in the output

Related: .ai/howto/how-to-create-a-pr.md
-->

